---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="About"
  description="Forge Kit is a single-developer catalog of skills, agents, MCP servers, hooks, commands, and tools for AI-assisted development. Built and maintained by Lucas Santana."
  titleSuffix="who built forgekit and why"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About Forge Kit</h1>
    <p class="lead-muted">A single-developer catalog of skills, sub-agents, MCP servers, hooks, commands, and tools for AI-assisted development.</p>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      Forge Kit is an opinionated, curated index of installable building blocks that work with Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, Cursor, and local LLMs. Every entry has been used in real projects — there's no "added for completeness" filler.
    </p>
    <p>
      Install with <code>npx forge-kit install &lt;id&gt;</code>. Skills, agents, hooks, commands, and tools land in <code>~/.claude/&lt;kind&gt;/</code>. MCP servers register with the local <code>mcp-context-forge</code> gateway via <code>npx forge-kit add-server &lt;id&gt;</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>What this isn't</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>An aggregator. The catalog is hand-curated and reviewed; nothing is auto-imported.</li>
      <li>A marketplace. Everything is MIT-licensed and free.</li>
      <li>Tied to a single provider. Provider tags route entries to Claude / Codex / Gemini / Cursor / Local on <a href="/providers/">/providers/</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Author</h2>
    <p>
      Built and maintained by <a href="https://github.com/LucasSantana-Dev" rel="noopener">Lucas Santana</a> — a software engineer working on AI-assisted development tooling. Most entries originated as patterns I needed across my own projects (Lucky, Craftvaria, homelab, ai-dev-toolkit) and were extracted into the catalog when they earned their second use.
    </p>

    <h2>How to contribute</h2>
    <p>
      The source lives at <a href="https://github.com/LucasSantana-Dev/forgekit" rel="noopener">github.com/LucasSantana-Dev/forgekit</a>. PRs welcome. See the <a href="https://github.com/LucasSantana-Dev/forgekit/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" rel="noopener">contribution guide</a> for entry conventions, schema, and the validation pipeline.
    </p>

    <h2>Links</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/contact/">Contact</a> — open issues, security disclosures, hello</li>
      <li><a href="/privacy/">Privacy policy</a> — what the site collects (spoiler: nothing)</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/LucasSantana-Dev/forgekit/blob/main/LICENSE" rel="noopener">License</a> — MIT</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>

